@startuml runtime-session
title Runtime View — Session Lifecycle

actor Developer
participant "Claude Code" as CC
participant "session-start.js" as SS
participant "Hook Scripts" as HS
participant "~/.claude/\nagents + skills" as Assets
participant "Learning\nFlywheel" as LF
participant "~/.claude/projects/\nsnapshots" as Snap

== Session Start ==
Developer -> CC: Opens project in Claude Code
CC -> SS: SessionStart hook fires
SS -> Snap: Read latest session snapshot
SS -> Assets: Load instinct overlays\n(~/.clarc/agent-instincts/)
SS -> CC: Inject context (≤3000 chars):\nopen tasks, recent files, SKILL_MAP,\ninstincts, rules version status

== During Session ==
Developer -> CC: Edits a file
CC -> HS: PostToolUse: Edit fires
HS -> HS: format-dispatch (auto-format)
HS -> HS: post-edit-typecheck (async)
HS -> HS: workflow-nudge (5 checks, cooldown)
HS -> HS: auto-checkpoint (git commit)

Developer -> CC: Runs /tdd or /code-review
CC -> Assets: Load tdd-guide.md or\ncode-reviewer.md agent
Assets -> CC: Agent instructions injected

Developer -> CC: Triggers context compaction
CC -> HS: PreCompact hook fires
HS -> Snap: Save structured snapshot\n(open tasks, touched files, exchanges)

== Session End ==
CC -> HS: Stop hook fires → session-end.js
HS -> LF: evaluate-session.js\n(quality gate on instinct extraction)
LF -> Snap: Write session evaluation
alt Monday
  LF -> LF: Weekly evolve batch\n(auto-cluster instincts)
end

@enduml
